text: Kushkul () is a rural locality (a village) in Tavtimanovsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 33 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 15 km from Iglino, 3.5 km from Tavtimanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Kushkul, Iglinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
